{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"In your example, you are recreating the material each frame. If you want to keep doing this, then you should call `map.material.dispose();` on it first, to make sure that it cleans up any resources.\r\n\r\n````\r\ndummyDataTex = new THREE.DataTexture( dummyRGBA, width, height, THREE.RGBAFormat );\r\ndummyDataTex.needsUpdate = true;\r\nmap.material.dipose();\r\nmap.material = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial( { map: dummyDataTex, side: THREE.FrontSide} )\r\n````\r\n\r\nSince the material doesn't change other than the map, a better way would be to just change the map.\r\n```\r\ndummyDataTex = new THREE.DataTexture( dummyRGBA, width, height, THREE.RGBAFormat );\r\ndummyDataTex.needsUpdate = true;\r\nif(map.material.map){\r\n  map.material.map.dispose(); \/\/clean up the previous texture\r\n}\r\nmap.material.map = dummyDataTex;\r\n````\r\n\r\nDoes that help your problem?","created_at":"2017-08-21T00:17:32.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11988#issuecomment-323621260","id":323621260,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11988","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMyMzYyMTI2MA==","updated_at":"2017-08-21T00:17:32.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/323621260","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/calrk\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/calrk\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatar